---
description:
Secure storage standards.

alwaysApply: true
---

# Secure Storage

Use flutter_secure_storage for sensitive data.

Never store secrets in Hive.

---

# Allowed Data

JWT

Refresh Token

Encryption Keys

Device Identifier

Biometric Flags

Nothing else.

---

# Forbidden Data

Passwords

PIN

Card Details

API Keys

Personal Documents

Never persist plaintext credentials.

---

# Token Lifecycle

Store:

Access Token

Refresh Token

Expiration

Repositories manage token refresh.

---

# Logout

Logout must:

Delete tokens

Delete session

Clear secure storage

Invalidate memory cache

---

# Biometric Authentication

Future support should integrate with secure storage.

Never bypass operating system security.

---

# Rotation

Support automatic token rotation.

Never continue using expired credentials.

---

# Failure Handling

If secure storage fails:

Invalidate session

Request login again

Do not continue with partially authenticated state.

---

# Testing

Test:

Token refresh

Corrupted storage

Logout

Expiration

Migration

---

# Cursor Instructions

Never read secure storage directly inside Widgets.

Access secure storage through repositories or authentication services only.